{In the following games, we shall take a look at Black's typical ways of
developing his queenside activity. Since we are currently focusing on the
aggressive systems, the model games will mainly feature positions with
castling on the opposite sides. The understanding of the typical strategies in
such positions is far more important than the knowledge of concrete theory.
Therefore, I suggest that you take a detailed look at the model games that
follow.}  *

[Event "Sofia MTel Masters 2nd"]
[Site "Sofia"]
[Date "2006.05.20"]
[Round "9"]
[White "Kamsky, Gata"]
[Black "Topalov, Veselin"]
[Result "0-1"]
[ECO "B97"]
[WhiteElo "2671"]
[BlackElo "2804"]
[Annotator "GM Ioannis Papaioannou"]
[PlyCount "58"]
[EventDate "2006.05.11"]
[EventType "tourn"]
[EventRounds "10"]
[EventCountry "BUL"]
