{A possible piece sacrifice on b5 should always be considered in the Sicilian
Defence. In most cases, this is even not a sacrifice since White takes three
pawns for the piece. For instance, in the position on the diagram, the sequence
} 1. Bxb5 $1 axb5 2. Ndxb5 Qb7 3. Qxd6 {tends to be quite favourable for White.
As a rule, the resulting endgames are almost hopeless for Black when White's
kingside structure is intact. The following two examples provide a good
illustration of this typical idea.} *

