{[%evp 0,115,31,45,53,49,71,69,69,30,30,28,46,41,66,51,89,72,56,48,53,32,88,32,
61,-22,-24,-13,-13,-23,-5,-11,-11,-11,-11,2,-3,0,6,-32,-18,-28,-36,-27,-13,-14,
0,4,-15,-13,-18,-14,-14,-21,18,38,37,42,47,74,77,83,89,79,93,5,30,30,125,147,
148,185,203,185,193,156,179,181,166,130,168,156,167,164,171,167,169,174,138,
176,176,160,160,180,178,176,184,195,222,230,303,315,315,348,341,351,344,307,
304,317,339,279,315,435,473,485,485,173] A successful Bxb5 sacrifice with all
the necessary conditions for white!} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6
5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e6 7. Be2 Qc7 8. Qd2 b5 9. f3 Nbd7 10. a3 h5 (10... Be7 11.
O-O-O O-O 12. Bxb5 axb5 13. Ndxb5 Qc6 14. Nxd6 Ba6) 11. O-O-O Rb8 (11... Be7
12. Bxb5 axb5 13. Ndxb5 Qa5 14. Nxd6+ Bxd6 15. Qxd6 Ra6 (15... Qa6 $4 16. Qxa6
Bxa6 17. b3 O-O 18. Kb2 Rfb8 19. Bd4 (19. Rd6 Ne5) 19... e5 20. Be3 Nb6 21.
Bxb6 Rxb6 22. a4) 16. Qd2 O-O 17. Kb1 Rc6 18. Nd5 Qxd2 19. Nxf6+ Nxf6 20. Rxd2
Ba6 21. b3 Rfc8 22. Kb2) 12. Bxb5 axb5 13. Ndxb5 {White wants to trade queens
or keep the more active queen!} Qb7 14. Qxd6 Bxd6 15. Nxd6+ Ke7 16. Nxb7 Bxb7 {
White is better here because he will start pushing his pawns and his pawn on
e4 is well-defended.} 17. Rd4 Rhd8 18. Rhd1 Ne5 19. a4 Rxd4 20. Bxd4 Nfd7 21.
b3 {Planning Kb2.} (21. f4 {is bad in principle! White wants a stable
situation over there.}) 21... g5 22. Nb5 g4 23. Bb2 gxf3 24. Ba3+ Kf6 25. gxf3
Kg5 26. Nd4 Ba6 27. Kb1 Rb7 28. Rg1+ Kf6 29. Bb2 Ke7 30. Rg5 h4 31. f4 Ng6 32.
Nxe6 fxe6 33. Rxg6 Nc5 34. f5 Kf7 35. Rf6+ Ke7 36. Rh6 Kf7 37. Rxh4 exf5 38.
exf5 Rd7 39. Bd4 Rd5 40. Rf4 Bc8 41. Bxc5 Rxc5 42. Kb2 Kf6 43. b4 Rc7 44. Kb3
Bxf5 45. c3 Rh7 46. b5 Ke5 47. Rd4 Rxh2 48. a5 Bh3 49. a6 Bf1 50. a7 Rh8 51.
Kb4 Bg2 52. Rd2 Bf3 53. Ka5 Rc8 54. Rd3 Bg2 55. Ka6 Rf8 56. Rd2 Ba8 57. c4 Rc8
58. c5 1-0

