{Black's position looks critical. How should he continue?} 1... Qe7 $3 {
stopping g4-g5 for some time and of course threatening Rxc3 without this Qe7
move, Black is much worse!} (1... Qb6 2. Nd5 $14 (2. g4 $3 $16 Rxc3 3. bxc3))
2. g3 (2. Qe1 {and now what?} Rxc3 $3 3. bxc3 Rc8 $132 (3... h5 $3 $132)) (2.
Nd5 Bxd5 3. Rxd5 Bxh4 $1 $15 4. Rhd1 Rfd8 (4... Qg5 5. Rxd6 Rfd8 6. Rxd8+ Rxd8
7. Rxd8+ Qxd8)) 2... Rxc3 $1 3. bxc3 Rc8 $1 {with good counter play for Black!}
4. Kb2 Rc4 $3 5. Nd2 Ra4 $3 $17 6. Ra1 d5 $1 {Halfhide-Antal 2017 (0-1)} *

