exf5 Qd5 12. Qh5 Qe4+ 13. Kd1)) 6... e5 7. Nb3 Be6 $6 8. Be3 (8. f4 $1 {
White should have played this! The Bishop on e6 is a bit premature.}) 8... Nbd7
9. f4 $6 (9. g4 h6 10. f4 $2 exf4 11. Bxf4 Nh5 12. Be3 Ng3 13. Rg1 Nxf1 14.
Kxf1 h5) 9... Rc8 $1 10. Qf3 (10. f5 $2 Rxc3 {As we have seen in the theory
section.} 11. bxc3 Nxe4 $17) 10... b5 (10... exf4 $1 {is also playable.} 11.
Bxf4 Ne5 12. Qe3 Be7 13. O-O-O Qc7) 11. f5 Bxb3 (11... Bc4 $1 $132 {Black
should have played Bc4 with good play!} 12. Bxc4 Rxc4 13. Nd2 (13. g4 h6 $132)
13... Rc7 $5 14. O-O-O Rxc3 $132) 12. cxb3 $2 (12. axb3 $1 $14 {This is the
best move.}) 12... d5 $3 $17 {very typical move.} 13. exd5 (13. Nxd5 Nxd5 14.
exd5 Bb4+ {With tremendous compensation.}) 13... Bb4 14. O-O-O O-O 15. Kb1 Bxc3
16. bxc3 Rxc3 17. Qe2 Ne4 18. Qe1 Rc8 19. Rc1 Ndf6 20. Rxc8 Qxc8 21. g4 Nxd5
22. Bg2 Nec3+ 23. Kb2 Nd1+ 24. Qxd1 Qc3+ 25. Kb1 Nxe3 26. Qe2 Rd8 27. Rc1 Qd4
28. a3 e4 0-1

