{The majority of the model games are dedicated to White's strategically most
ambitious plan based on the Nd5 jump. After the moves} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4
cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. f3 h5 {[%cal Gc3d5,Ge6d5]
White can play Nd5 either immediately or after the preparatory 9.Qd2.
Sometimes, the knight jump is preceeded even by 9.Be2. As a rule, Black reacts
with ...Bxd5 followed by ...g7-g6. The arising positions are strategically
complex and imbalanced. By studying the model games, you will get better
understanding of the typical positional and tactical subtleties.} *

