45,-15,18,18,23,-6,22,-6,-1,3,-7,-33,-22,-137,-155,-155,-175,-211,-209,-224,
-221,-263,-245,-278]} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6.
Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. Qd2 Nbd7 9. f3 h5 10. Nd5 Bxd5 11. exd5 g6 12. O-O-O Bg7
13. Kb1 O-O {This is considered to be a bit premature because of a fast h3-g4,
however, this is just a blitz game and a great demonstration of the typical
ideas for black ! We are faced with a fast Na5, we play Qc7 and a very fast
e5-e4 !} (13... Qc7 {is a more common move. Black is delaying castling as
White is short of moves.}) 14. Na5 (14. h3 $1 $36 {intending g4 and attack.})
14... Qc7 15. c4 $2 e4 $1 $17 {Black is almost winning! White's Knight is far
from the center and we exploit it wisely.} 16. Be2 (16. f4 Ng4 $19 {Typical
ideas in action!} 17. Bg1 e3 18. Qe1 Nc5 19. Nb3 Na4) 16... exf3 17. gxf3 Rfe8
18. Bd4 Rxe2 19. Qxe2 Qxa5 20. f4 Re8 21. Qg2 Ng4 22. Bxg7 Kxg7 23. Qd2 0-1

