Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. f3 h5 9. Qd2 Nbd7 10. Nd5 Bxd5 11. exd5 g6 12.
O-O-O Qc7 13. Kb1 Bg7 14. c4 O-O 15. h3 b6 {planning Nc5} (15... a5 $1 $132)
16. g4 Nc5 {This is a kind of positional battle where both sides don't have
enough attack.} 17. Rg1 (17. Nc1 b5 {We are ready to open up more lines now.}
18. cxb5 axb5 19. Bxb5) 17... a5 18. Na1 a4 19. Nc2 a3 20. Nxa3 Rxa3 21. bxa3
Ra8 {The side which has sacrificed the exchanged wants to have opposite
cloured Bishops to create counterplay easily.} 22. Bg5 h4 {It is important to
block the files to attack.} 23. Qc1 e4 24. f4 e3 {Intending Ne4. This is how
you should play the Najdorf.} 25. Bxf6 Bxf6 26. Qxe3 Qd7 27. Re1 Na4 28. Rc1
Re8 29. Qb3 Nc5 30. Qc2 Re3 31. g5 Bg7 32. Rg2 Ne4 33. Qd1 Qf5 34. Bd3 Qxf4 35.
Bxe4 Qxe4+ 36. Qc2 Qe5 0-1

