6. Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. f3 h5 9. Qd2 Nbd7 10. Nd5 Bxd5 11. exd5 g6 12. Be2 Bg7
13. O-O b6 $1 14. a4 O-O 15. a5 b5 16. c4 bxc4 17. Bxc4 Qc7 {Following our
typical plan of Qb7} 18. Rfc1 Qb7 19. Qd3 $2 e4 $3 $19 {This central break is
very important. Black is already winning!} 20. fxe4 Ne5 21. Qc2 (21. Qe2 Nxc4 {
The best move tactically.} 22. Qxc4 Ng4 23. Bd4 Rfc8 24. Qd3 Bxd4+ 25. Nxd4
