{[%evp 0,124,21,20,37,44,65,51,51,24,37,24,49,41,41,34,34,29,55,52,54,27,37,37,
45,37,52,44,71,41,43,49,62,40,46,24,44,12,42,33,33,31,10,21,24,32,38,26,21,32,
32,35,26,20,30,14,14,7,17,16,13,13,11,11,0,0,0,12,0,0,8,0,16,20,15,15,16,19,7,
-5,9,0,0,1,24,-71,-59,-71,-71,-62,-54,-54,-42,-42,-46,-47,-52,-59,-35,-51,-47,
-47,-47,-106,-99,-121,-112,-108,-104,-115,-117,-123,-129,-170,-172,-172,-172,
-173,-187,-226,-248,-248,-248,-252,-235,-234,-234] Another perfect game by the
Najdorf expert Ivan Saric.} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6
6. Be3 e5 7. Nb3 Be6 8. f3 h5 (8... Be7 9. Qd2 O-O 10. O-O-O Nbd7 11. g4 b5 12.
g5 Nh5 13. Nd5 Bxd5 14. exd5 Qe8 15. Na5 Bd8 16. Nc6 Bb6) 9. Qd2 (9. Nd5 Bxd5
10. exd5 Nbd7 11. Qd2 g6) 9... Nbd7 10. Nd5 Bxd5 11. exd5 g6 12. Be2 (12. Na5
Qc7 13. Be2 Bg7 14. O-O e4 {Typical break to meet Na5 ideas.} 15. f4 Ng4 16.
Bxg4 hxg4) 12... Bg7 13. O-O b6 $1 {The most accurate move after 0-0} 14. a4
O-O {Our common plan in these positions is Nh7 - f5 - Bf6 - Bg5 or Re8} 15. c4
(15. a5 b5 $15 16. c4 bxc4 17. Bxc4 Qc7 $1 {planning Qb7 to pressurize the
d5-pawn.} 18. Rac1 (18. Rfc1 Qb7 $15 19. Rc3 (19. Qd3 $4 e4 20. fxe4 Ne5 $19
21. Qe2 Nxc4 22. Qxc4 Ng4 23. Bd4 Rfc8 24. Qd3 Bxd4+ 25. Nxd4 Qxb2 $19) 19...
Rfc8) 18... Qb7 $15) 15... a5 {common way to stop a5.} (15... Nc5 {is also
possible.} 16. Nxc5 bxc5 17. a5 {should be played to plan b4 in the future.})
16. Rae1 {White has no clear plan.} (16. f4 Ne4 {Black has very strong play in
the central squares.} (16... exf4 $1 {stockfish} 17. Bxf4 {In such positions,
all the squares on the e-file in White's camp are weak. Black is better
because of this.} Ne4 (17... Nc5 18. Nd4 (18. Nxc5 bxc5 19. Bf3 Qb6 20. Rae1
Rfe8 21. Kh1 Nd7 22. b3 Ne5 23. Bxe5 Rxe5 24. Rxe5 Bxe5)) 18. Qc2 Ndc5 19. Nxc5
Nxc5 $15 {Black is better as White has a poor Bishop on e2.}) 17. Qc2 f5 (17...
Ndc5 18. Nxc5 Nxc5 19. f5) 18. fxe5 dxe5 19. d6 $1 Ndc5 $132) 16... Qc7 17. Kh1
Rae8 {Bringing all the pieces in the play.} 18. Qd1 h4 {Black could also play:
Nc5 or Nh7 or Kh7-Bh67} 19. f4 (19. Bg5 h3 20. gxh3 Nh5 {with compensation.}) (
19. h3 Nh5 20. Bf2 (20. Bg5 Ng3+ (20... Qd8 $5) (20... Bf6)) 20... Ng3+ 21.
Bxg3 hxg3) 19... exf4 20. Bxf4 Ne4 21. Bd3 Nec5 22. Nxc5 Nxc5 23. b3 Qd8 {
Black wants to trade Rooks now.} 24. Bc2 f5 $1 {intending Qf6} 25. Qd2 Qf6 26.
Bg5 Rxe1 27. Rxe1 Qc3 28. Qxc3 Bxc3 {White's main problem in this endgame is
the poor light squared Bishop.} 29. Re2 Bf6 $1 30. Bf4 Rd8 31. Kg1 Kf7 32. Kf2
Bd4+ $1 33. Kf3 Kf6 $1 34. g4 hxg3 35. h4 Rd7 36. Bg5+ Kf7 37. Kxg3 Bf6 $1 38.
Bd2 Rd8 39. h5 Be5+ 40. Kf3 gxh5 41. Rg2 Rh8 42. Bxf5 Nxb3 43. Be6+ Ke7 44.
Bg5+ Bf6 45. Be3 Nc5 46. Bxc5 bxc5 47. Rg8 Rh6 48. Ra8 Bc3 49. Ra7+ Kf6 50.
Rf7+ Kg5 51. Kg2 Rh8 52. Rf5+ Kg6 53. Rf3 Be5 54. Bd7 Rb8 55. Bb5 Rg8 56. Kh3
Kh6 57. Bd7 Rg1 58. Be8 Kg5 59. Bd7 Rc1 60. Rf5+ Kg6 61. Rf8 Rc3+ 62. Kg2 Rxc4
0-1

