{The remaining model games feature the plans without Nd5 in the position
arising after} 1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Be3 e5 7.
Nb3 Be6 8. f3 h5 {White often plays Qd2 and 0-0-0 without Nd5. In this case,
he usually tries to attack on the kingside starting with h2-h3. In the
following model games, you will see not only how Black should attack on the
queenside, but also how to deal with White's kingside attacking ideas.} *

