{The first couple of model games feature the position arising after} 1. e4 c5
2. Nf3 d6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. h3 e5 7. Nde2 h5 {As we know
from the theoretical file, White's most challenging approach is to fight for
the d5-square by means Bg5 followed by Bxf6 and Nd5. Additionally, the
alternative plans such as 8.g3 and even 8.Ng1 are covered in the model games.}
