{[%evp 0,105,24,13,37,50,78,74,74,53,59,40,47,25,25,2,35,35,35,20,20,31,36,9,4,
-6,21,0,0,-24,-2,-12,-7,-29,-27,-14,-10,-4,4,-5,0,-34,78,-70,-70,-138,-32,-49,
-66,-73,-40,-60,-60,-178,-166,-180,-152,-176,-133,-128,-132,-125,-148,-165,-41,
-37,-43,-54,-52,-56,-54,-54,-64,-51,-62,-81,57,-107,-19,-21,50,-146,-21,-111,
-94,-109,-21,-21,51,29,57,50,67,50,50,41,214,-47,41,41,189,202,428,467,960,960,
982,1099] We will see in this game how the 8.Bg5, 11.Qd3 line works perfectly
for Black. We will also witness a hidden idea worth remembering.} 1. e4 c5 2.
Nc3 a6 3. Nf3 d6 4. d4 cxd4 5. Nxd4 Nf6 6. h3 e5 7. Nde2 h5 8. Bg5 Be6 9. Bxf6
Qxf6 10. Nd5 Qd8 11. Qd3 Nd7 12. O-O-O g6 13. Kb1 Nc5 14. Qa3 Bg7 15. Nec3 O-O
{I would hate to play this position as White. He has no active plan whatsoever
and Black simply prepares a queenside expansion.} 16. h4 b5 17. Be2 Rb8 18. b4
Bxd5 (18... a5 $3 $19 {AN IMPORTANT IDEA TO REMEMBER!}) 19. Rxd5 Qc7 20. Rhd1
Rfc8 21. Qb2 Ne6 22. R5d3 Nd4 23. Nd5 Qxc2+ 24. Qxc2 Rxc2 25. Rxd4 Rxe2 26.
R4d2 Rxe4 27. g3 Kf8 28. a3 Rc8 29. Nb6 Rc6 30. Rxd6 Rxd6 31. Rxd6 Rd4 32. Rxd4
