{Let's take a look at the position on the diagram. As we have seen in the
theoretical file, the setups based on Qf3 are very challenging. Very often the
queen goes to g3 from where it exerts pressure on the kingside. A typicla
follow up after Qg3 is the move Bh6. As we will see, this attacking concept is
not that dangerous as it might look at first sight. For instance, if in this
position, White plays} 1. Bh6 {we immediately respond by} Ne8 {[%cal Gc8d7,
Gb8c6] Black is ready to proceed with ...Bd7 followed by ...Nc6. After kicking
the d4-knight back, we can consider advancing the queenside pawns. The first
model games, are dedicated to similar type of positions.} *

