{Let's take a closer look at this theoretical position. Black cannot play the
usually desirable ...Bb7 in view of Bxe6. At the same time, White is
threatening e4-e5. A typical idea, therefore, would be} 1... Qb6 {attacking
the knight and getting ready to answer e4-e5 with ...Bb7.} 2. Be3 Qb7 {[%cal
Ge8g8,Gb8d7,Gd7c5] Remember this maneuver. The queen is excellently placed on
b7. We are now ready to increase the pressure on e4 by means of ...0-0
followed by ...Nbd7-c5. The following model games will feature exactly the
maneuver ...Qb6-b7.} *

