{On the board, we can see one of Black's dream positions in the line with 6.
Bc4. Usually, the goal of our queenside play is kicking the c3-knight back by
means of ...b5-b4. Once the knight goes far away from the centre, we can also
deliever the advance ...d6-d5. For instance, in this position, the play might
continue} 1... b4 $1 2. axb4 axb4 3. Ne2 e5 $1 {[%cal Gd6d5] with ...d6-d5 to
follow. The immediate ...d6-d5 would have been met by e4-e5. The following
model games will provide you with a better understanding of the advance ...
b5-b4.} *

