Bc4 e6 7. Bb3 b5 8. Qf3 Bb7 9. O-O Nc6 10. Nxc6 (10. Nxe6 fxe6 11. Bxe6 Nd4 {
is too much for White.} 12. Qh3 Nxe6 13. Qxe6+ Be7 $19) 10... Bxc6 11. Re1 (11.
Qg3 {trying to stop Be7, but here White has to consider what happens after 11..
.b4. Good to know is that a queen on g3 normally doesn't stop Be7.} b4 (11...
Be7 12. Qxg7 Rg8 13. Qh6 Rg6 14. Qh3 b4 15. Na4 Nxe4 $19)) 11... Be7 12. a3 O-O
13. Bf4 Qc7 14. Rad1 (14. e5 Bxf3 (14... dxe5 15. Bxe5 Qb7 16. Qg3 g6 17. Rad1
{[%csl Rb3]} Rad8 {and we start to exchange pieces, there's no attack anymore
and White can only wonder what to do with the a2-bishop.} (17... Nd7 18. Bd6
Nc5) 18. Ba2 Rxd1 19. Rxd1 Rd8 20. Rxd8+ Bxd8)) 14... Rfd8 $15 (14... Rad8 $15
15. Ba2 Qb7) 15. g4 a5 16. g5 Nd7 17. Qh5 Nf8 $17 18. Rd3 b4 19. axb4 axb4 20.
Nd1 Qb7 21. Rd4 Ra1 22. Bd2 d5 23. e5 Bc5 24. Rd3 d4 25. Qg4 Bb5 26. h4 Qa6 27.
Qg3 Ng6 28. h5 Ne7 29. Kh2 Nf5 30. Qh3 g6 31. Rg1 Bf8 32. Bf4 Bxd3 33. cxd3 Bg7
34. Re1 Rc8 35. Qf3 gxh5 36. Rg1 h4 37. Qe4 Qc6 38. Qxc6 Rxc6 39. Kg2 Rc5 0-1

