cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 a6 6. Bg5 Nbd7 7. f4 Qa5 8. Qf3 h6 9. Bh4 e5 10. Nb3
Qc7 11. f5 Be7 {I recommend 11...b5, but this is also good. Black stops the
Nd5 idea on account of ...Nxd5 winning a piece.} 12. a4 b6 13. O-O-O $6 {
The problem with the long castle connected with a4 is that sooner or later the
...b5 sacrifice to open White's king will come.} Bb7 14. Kb1 O-O 15. Nd2 $2 {
This move is slow and highly aggravates White's problems.} b5 $1 {As mentioned
previously. Black's attack is already objectively decisive!} 16. Bf2 Rfc8 17.
axb5 {White chooses to open the a-file and loses to a sacrificial attack.
White is pretty helpless anyway at this point.} axb5 18. Bxb5 Nc5 19. Bxc5 Qxc5
20. Nb3 Qa7 21. Rhe1 Rxc3 22. bxc3 d5 23. exd5 Nxd5 24. Rxd5 Bg5 25. Na5 Bxd5
0-1

